Simple Multithreader

Divanshu Jain 2024198
Parth Choyal  2024403


How to compile

1. make

This builds Binary of programs:
- vector   Parallel vector addition
- matrix   Parallel matrix multiplication

2.
./vector <numThreads> <size>
./matrix <numThreads> <size>

Eg:
    ./vector 4 48000000    
    ./matrix 8 1024        


\parallel_for (1D)

Parallelizes a single loop across multiple threads.

    void parallel_for(int low, int high,std::function<void(int)> &&lambda,int numThreads);

Parameters:
- low       //Starting index 
- high      //Ending index
- lambda    //Function to execute for each iteration receives index i
- numThreads //Total number of threads (including main thread)




\parallel_for (2D)

Parallelizes nested loops by distributing outer loop iterations across threads.

    void parallel_for(int low1, int high1, int low2, int high2,std::function<void(int, int)> &&lambda,int numThreads);

Parameters:
- low1, high1  Outer loop range 
- low2, high2  Inner loop range 
- lambda       Function to execute for each iteration receives indices i, j
- numThreads   Total number of threads (including main thread)




- Thread Management: Creates numThreads-1 worker threads; main thread 
                     participates in computation
- Work Distribution: Divides iterations evenly across threads with load balancing
- Timing           : Prints execution time for each parallel_for call
- Error Handling   : Validates inputs and handles thread creation/joining 
                     failures


\To clean all binary files

make clean


